props.name: by
props.description: Use this to compare objects by a particular field, or pass your own comparison function for complete control over how objects are compared.

props.name: defaultOpen
props.description: The open state of the select when it is initially rendered. Use when you do not need to control its open state.

props.name: defaultValue
props.description: The value of the select when initially rendered. Use when you do not need to control the state of the Select

props.name: dir
props.description: The reading direction of the combobox when applicable. <br> If omitted, inherits globally from ConfigProvider or assumes LTR (left-to-right) reading mode.

props.name: disabled
props.description: When true, prevents the user from interacting with Select

props.name: modelValue
props.description: The controlled value of the Select. Can be bind as v-model.

props.name: multiple
props.description: Whether multiple options can be selected or not.

props.name: name
props.description: The name of the field. Submitted with its owning form as part of a name/value pair.

props.name: open
props.description: The controlled open state of the Select. Can be bind as v-model:open.

props.name: required
props.description: When true, indicates that the user must set the value before the owning form can be submitted.
